Sentencas: Planar, Cu-containing Gadolinia-doped ceria anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells to be used at intermediate temperature (500-750 C-omicron) were produced in the present work, The Intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells were fabricated using Li2O as sintering aid for Gadolinia-doped ceria, varying the anode-to-electrolyte thickness ratio (r) from 2 to 10 and the CuO content in the anode from 45 vol% to 55 vol%.
Titulo: Effect of anode thickness and Cu content on consolidation and performance of planar copper-based anode-supported SOFC

Sentencas: Co-sintering of the thermo-pressed green cells was carried out at 900 C-omicron for 3 h. The electrolyte densification was favoured by increasing the r value, this being accounted for the enhanced compressive stresses induced by the supporting anode on the electrolyte upon sintering.
Titulo: Effect of anode thickness and Cu content on consolidation and performance of planar copper-based anode-supported SOFC

Sentencas: Larger CuO content positively influences the overall cell performance, due to the improved electronic conductivity of the anode.
Titulo: Effect of anode thickness and Cu content on consolidation and performance of planar copper-based anode-supported SOFC

Sentencas: Nevertheless, CuO concentration cannot exceed 50 vol% because of the tensile stresses (and corresponding flaws) generated in the electrolyte for larger amount.
Titulo: Effect of anode thickness and Cu content on consolidation and performance of planar copper-based anode-supported SOFC

Sentencas: IT-SOFC containing 50 vol% CuO was characterized by an Open Circuit Voltage approximate to 0.82 V and a maximum power density of 200 mW cm(-2) at 700 C-omicron.
Titulo: Effect of anode thickness and Cu content on consolidation and performance of planar copper-based anode-supported SOFC
